    "Consequently, human-automation trust, akin to interpersonal trust, constitutes a psychological state that influences behaviors.",
    "Trust is crucial for the adoption of automation technologies, and a deficiency of trust in automation can lead to reduced reliance on these systems (Lee and See, 2004).",
    "Since the 1980s, with the widespread adoption of automation technology and its increasing complexity, research in human-automation interaction, technology acceptance models, and human-automation trust has drastically expanded.",
